<p>The <code>increment</code> tag increments a variable by 1.</p>

<h2>Basic Increment</h2>
<pre>{open}set counter=0{close}
Before: {open}$counter{close}
{open}increment $counter{close}
After: {open}$counter{close}</pre>
{set counter=0}
<p>Before: {$counter}</p>
{increment $counter}
<p>After: {$counter}</p>

<h2>Multiple Increments</h2>
<pre>{open}set n=0{close}
{open}increment $n{close} n = {open}$n{close}
{open}increment $n{close} n = {open}$n{close}
{open}increment $n{close} n = {open}$n{close}</pre>
{set n=0}
<p>{increment $n}n = {$n}</p>
<p>{increment $n}n = {$n}</p>
<p>{increment $n}n = {$n}</p>

<h2>Increment in Loop</h2>
<pre>{open}set i=1{close}
{open}while $i <= 5{close}
  Number: {open}$i{close}
  {open}increment $i{close}
{open}/while{close}</pre>
{set i=1}
<ul>
{while $i <= 5}
  <li>Number: {$i}</li>
  {increment $i}
{/while}
</ul>

<h2>Increment Creates Variable</h2>
<pre>{open}increment $newVar{close}
Value: {open}$newVar{close}</pre>
<p>Incrementing undefined variable creates it with value 1:</p>
{increment $newVar}
<p>Value: {$newVar}</p>

<h2>Increment Existing PHP Variable</h2>
<pre>PHP set $startValue = 10
{open}increment $startValue{close}
After: {open}$startValue{close}</pre>
<p>$startValue from PHP: {$startValue}</p>
{increment $startValue}
<p>After increment: {$startValue}</p>

<h2>Counting Items</h2>
<pre>{open}set itemCount=0{close}
{open}sequence '1..5'{close}
  {open}increment $itemCount{close}
{open}/sequence{close}
Total items: {open}$itemCount{close}</pre>
{set itemCount=0}
{sequence '1..5'}
  {increment $itemCount}
{/sequence}
<p>Total items counted: {$itemCount}</p>
